quran[182]{c,v,t}:
  37,1,By those ňĻangelsňļ lined up in ranks
  37,2,and those who diligently drive ňĻthe cloudsňļ
  37,3,and those who recite the Reminder
  37,4,Surely your God is One
  37,5,"ňĻHe isňļ the Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between, and the Lord of all points of sunrise"
  37,6,"Indeed, We have adorned the lowest heaven with the stars for decoration"
  37,7,and ňĻforňļ protection from every rebellious devil
  37,8,They cannot listen to the highest assembly ňĻof angelsňļ for they are pelted from every side
  37,9,ňĻfiercelyňļ driven away. And they will suffer an everlasting torment
  37,10,But whoever manages to stealthily eavesdrop is ňĻinstantlyňļ pursued by a piercing flare
  37,11,"So ask them ňĻO Prophetňļ, which is harder to create: them or other marvels of Our creation?¬†Indeed, We created them from a sticky clay"
  37,12,"In fact, you are astonished ňĻby their denialňļ, while they ridicule ňĻyouňļ"
  37,13,"When they are reminded, they are never mindful"
  37,14,"And whenever they see a sign, they make fun of it"
  37,15,"saying, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but pure magic"
  37,16,"When we are dead and reduced to dust and bones, will we really be resurrected"
  37,17,And our forefathers as well?‚ÄĚ
  37,18,"Say, ‚ÄúYes! And you will be fully humbled.‚ÄĚ"
  37,19,"It will only take one Blast,¬†then at once they will see ňĻit allňļ"
  37,20,"They will cry, ‚ÄúOh, woe to us! This is the Day of Judgment!‚ÄĚ"
  37,21,"ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúThis is the Day of ňĻFinalňļ Decision which you used to deny.‚ÄĚ"
  37,22,"ňĻAllah will say to the angels,ňļ ‚ÄúGather ňĻallňļ the wrongdoers along with their peers, and whatever they used to worship"
  37,23,"instead of Allah, then lead them ňĻallňļ to the path of Hell"
  37,24,"And detain them, for they must be questioned.‚ÄĚ"
  37,25,"ňĻThen they will be asked,ňļ ‚ÄúWhat is the matter with you that you can no longer help each other?‚ÄĚ"
  37,26,"In fact, on that Day they will be ňĻfullyňļ submissive"
  37,27,"They will turn on each other, throwing blame"
  37,28,"The misled will say, ‚ÄúIt was you who deluded us away from what is right.‚ÄĚ"
  37,29,"The misleaders will reply, ‚ÄúNo! You disbelieved on your own"
  37,30,"We had no authority over you. In fact, you yourselves were a transgressing people"
  37,31,"The decree of our Lord has come to pass against us ňĻallňļ: we will certainly taste ňĻthe punishmentňļ"
  37,32,"We caused you to deviate, for we ourselves were deviant.‚ÄĚ"
  37,33,Surely on that Day they will ňĻallňļ share in the punishment
  37,34,That is certainly how We deal with the wicked
  37,35,"For whenever it was said to them ňĻin the worldňļ, ‚ÄúThere is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Allah,‚ÄĚ they acted arrogantly"
  37,36,"and argued, ‚ÄúShould we really abandon our gods for a mad poet?‚ÄĚ"
  37,37,"In fact, he came with the truth, confirming ňĻearlierňļ messengers"
  37,38,You will certainly taste the painful torment
  37,39,and will only be rewarded for what you used to do
  37,40,But not the chosen servants of Allah
  37,41,They will have a known provision
  37,42,fruits ňĻof every typeňļ.¬†And they will be honoured
  37,43,in the Gardens of Bliss
  37,44,facing each other on thrones
  37,45,A drink ňĻof pure wineňļ will be passed around to them from a flowing stream
  37,46,"crystal-white, delicious to drink"
  37,47,"It will neither harm ňĻthemňļ, nor will they be intoxicated by it"
  37,48,And with them will be maidens of modest gaze and gorgeous eyes
  37,49,as if they were pristine pearls
  37,50,Then they will turn to one another inquisitively
  37,51,"One of them will say, ‚ÄúI once had a companion ňĻin the worldňļ"
  37,52,"who used to ask ňĻmeňļ, ‚ÄėDo you actually believe ňĻin resurrectionňļ"
  37,53,"When we are dead and reduced to dust and bones, will we really be brought to judgment?‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  37,54,"He will ňĻthenňļ ask, ‚ÄúWould you care to see ňĻhis fateňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  37,55,Then he ňĻand the othersňļ will look and spot him in the midst of the Hellfire
  37,56,"He will ňĻthenňļ say, ‚ÄúBy Allah! You nearly ruined me"
  37,57,"Had it not been for the grace of my Lord, I ňĻtooňļ would have certainly been among those brought ňĻto Hellňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  37,58,"ňĻThen he will ask his fellow believers,ňļ ‚ÄúCan you imagine that we will never die"
  37,59,"except our first death, nor be punished ňĻlike the othersňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  37,60,This is truly the ultimate triumph
  37,61,For such ňĻhonourňļ all should strive
  37,62,Is this ňĻblissňļ a better accommodation or the tree of Zaqq√Ľm
  37,63,We have surely made it a test for the wrongdoers
  37,64,"Indeed, it is a tree that grows in the depths of Hell"
  37,65,bearing fruit like devils‚Äô heads
  37,66,"The evildoers will certainly ňĻbe left toňļ eat from it, filling up their bellies with it"
  37,67,Then on top of that they will be given a blend of boiling drink
  37,68,Then they will ultimately return to ňĻtheir place inňļ Hell
  37,69,"Indeed, they found their forefathers astray"
  37,70,so they rushed in their footsteps
  37,71,And surely most of the earlier generations had strayed before them
  37,72,although We had certainly sent warners among them
  37,73,See then what was the end of those who had been warned
  37,74,But not the chosen servants of Allah
  37,75,"Indeed, Noah cried out to Us, and how excellent are We in responding"
  37,76,We delivered him and his family¬†from the great distress
  37,77,and made his descendants the sole survivors
  37,78,And We blessed him ňĻwith honourable mentionňļ among later generations
  37,79,‚ÄúPeace be upon Noah among all peoples.‚ÄĚ
  37,80,"Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,81,ňĻForňļ he was truly one of Our faithful servants
  37,82,Then We drowned the others
  37,83,"And indeed, one of those who followed his way was Abraham"
  37,84,ňĻRememberňļ when he came to his Lord with a pure heart
  37,85,"and said to his father and his people, ‚ÄúWhat are you worshipping"
  37,86,Is it false gods that you desire instead of Allah
  37,87,What then do you expect from the Lord of all worlds?‚ÄĚ
  37,88,He later looked up to the stars ňĻin contemplationňļ
  37,89,"then said, ‚ÄúI am really sick.‚ÄĚ"
  37,90,So they turned their backs on him and went away
  37,91,"Then he ňĻstealthilyňļ advanced towards their gods, and said ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWill you not eat ňĻyour offeringsňļ"
  37,92,What is wrong with you that you cannot speak?‚ÄĚ
  37,93,"Then he swiftly turned on them, striking ňĻthemňļ with his right hand"
  37,94,"Later, his people came rushing towards him ňĻfuriouslyňļ"
  37,95,"He argued, ‚ÄúHow can you worship what you carve ňĻwith your own handsňļ"
  37,96,when it is Allah Who created you and whatever you do?‚ÄĚ
  37,97,"They said ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúBuild him a furnace and cast him into the blazing fire.‚ÄĚ"
  37,98,"And so they sought to harm him, but We made them inferior"
  37,99,"He later said, ‚ÄúI am leaving ňĻin obedienceňļ to my Lord. He will guide me"
  37,100,My Lord! Bless me with righteous offspring.‚ÄĚ
  37,101,So We gave him good news of a forbearing son
  37,102,"Then when the boy reached the age to work with him, Abraham said, ‚ÄúO my dear son! I have seen in a dream that I ňĻmustňļ sacrifice you. So tell me what you think.‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúO my dear father! Do as you are commanded. Allah willing, you will find me steadfast.‚ÄĚ"
  37,103,"Then when they submitted ňĻto Allah‚Äôs Willňļ, and Abraham laid him on the side of his forehead ňĻfor sacrificeňļ"
  37,104,"We called out to him, ‚ÄúO Abraham"
  37,105,"You have already fulfilled the vision.‚ÄĚ Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,106,That was truly a revealing test
  37,107,And We ransomed his son with a great sacrifice
  37,108,and blessed Abraham ňĻwith honourable mentionňļ among later generations
  37,109,‚ÄúPeace be upon Abraham.‚ÄĚ
  37,110,This is how We reward the good-doers
  37,111,He was truly one of Our faithful servants
  37,112,"We ňĻlaterňļ gave him good news of Isaac‚ÄĒa prophet, and one of the righteous"
  37,113,"We blessed him¬†and Isaac as well. Some of their descendants did good, while others clearly wronged themselves"
  37,114,And We certainly showed favour to Moses and Aaron
  37,115,and delivered them and their people from the great distress
  37,116,We helped them so it was they who prevailed
  37,117,We gave them the clear Scripture
  37,118,and guided them to the Straight Path
  37,119,And We blessed them ňĻwith honourable mentionňļ among later generations
  37,120,‚ÄúPeace be upon Moses and Aaron.‚ÄĚ
  37,121,"Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,122,They were truly ňĻtwoňļ of Our faithful servants
  37,123,And Elias was indeed one of the messengers
  37,124,"ňĻRememberňļ when he said to his people, ‚ÄúWill you not fear ňĻAllahňļ"
  37,125,Do you call upon ňĻthe idol ofňļ Ba‚Äôl¬†and abandon the Best of Creators‚ÄĒ
  37,126,"Allah, your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers?‚ÄĚ"
  37,127,"But they rejected him, so they will certainly be brought ňĻfor punishmentňļ"
